0009|- [HelpText]
0010|#FILE SAVE MAT <matrix file> TO <Survo data file>
S   |               <           >    <               >
0011|*saves a matrix file to a Survo data file.
0012|*The first line (row) to be copied from the matrix file is given by the
0013|*specification FIRST=<# of first line>. Default is FIRST=1.
S   |                     <               >
0014|*Similarly, the last row to be copied is given by LAST=<# of last row>.
S   |                                                       <             >
0015|*Default is the last row in the matrix.
0016|*The columns of the matrix are copied to variables of the data file
0017|*according to the column labels (8 first characters of names should
0018|*match). If a variable corresponding to a certain matrix column does not
0019|*exist, a new numeric variable is created. The type (1,2,4 or 8) of
0020|*new variables can be given by TYPE=<type>. Default is TYPE=4.
S   |                                    <    >
0021|*Without a MATCH specification, all the rows will be copied to the Survo
0022|*data file as new observations. If the first field in the data file is
0023|*of the string type, the row labels will be copied to this field (as
0024|*names of new observations).
0025|*However, if a specification LABEL=<name_of_variable> is given, the row
S   |                                   <                >
0026|*labels are saved in this variable.
0027|*If the Survo data file does not exist, a new file will be automatic-
0028|*ally created with suitable dimensions.
0030|*To extend existing observations in the Survo data file, a MATCH
0031|*specification can be given.
0032|*If MATCH is omitted, all the rows will be copied to the Survo
0033|*data file as new observations.
0034|*MATCH=<name of a string field>
S   |       <                      >
0035|*specifies the field in the Survo data file whose contents should be
0036|*equal to the label of the row to be copied.
0037|*The order of the observations in the matrix file and in the data file must
0038|*be same.
0040|*By giving MATCH=# the observations are copied from the matrix file
0041|*to the data file without a match variable, but the first row
0042|*to be copied will placed as the first observation in the data file.
