0056|- [HelpText]
0057|*Matrix expressions in the Survo matrix interpreter
0059|*The basic MAT operations related to standard arithmetics are typically
0060|*binary (i.e. of the form MAT C=A+B) and thus only two operands are
0061|*in use. However, SURVO MM provides a matrix preprocessor for
0062|*manipulating more complicated expressions like
0063|*MAT D2=(X-MY)'*INV(S)*(X-MY)
0064|*The preprocessor converts such expressions automatically into basic
0065|*MAT commands. The above MAT command is translated within the matrix
0066|*interpreter into 4 MAT commands
0067|*%%1=X-MY
0068|*%%2=INV(S)
0069|*%%2=%%2*%%1
0070|*D2=%%1'*%%2
0071|*where %%1,%%2,... are temporary matrix files on the current data path.
0073|*The preprocessor is available in SURVO MM when the system parameter
0074|*`mat_parser' (in SURVO.APU) is set to a positive value or command
0075|*SYSTEM mat_parser=<positive_integer>
S   |                   <                >
0076|*is activated. The value of mat_parser should exceed the maximum length
0077|*of the series of translated MAT commands and twice the length of the
0078|*longest matrix expression. mat_parser=4000 (default) is recommended.
0080|*The matrix expressions may contain all expressions appearing in the MAT
0081|*commands of the form
0082|*MAT C=function_of(A,B,...).
0083|*The preprocessor does not optimize the order of operations. Typically
0084|*operations are carried out from the left to the rigth unless otherwise
0085|*stated by the user by extra parentheses.
0086|*Example:
0087|*MAT Y=A*(B*(C*Y))
0089|*The translated MAT commands of the last activated general expression
0090|*are saved in the text file SURVOMAT.TMP in the subdirectory for
0091|*temporary files of Survo.
0092|*Thus the user may inspect how the preprocessor works by studying this
0093|*file (using SHOW, for example).
0095|*Generalized matrix expressions (of more than 2 operands) cannot be
0096|*used in matrix chains (.MTX files) but they are allowed in
0097|*continuous activations (with F2 ESC) and in sucros.
0098|*In general it is better to make matrix programs as sucros and
0099|*not as matrix chains (.MTX files).
